- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a likely category as the paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems, which involve discrete structures and mathematical techniques. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper involves designing algorithms for routing problems, which can be modeled as games between the routing agent and the environment. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper deals with routing problems that are relevant to autonomous robots and vehicles, which require efficient algorithms to navigate through complex environments. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper involves analyzing the complexity of approximation algorithms for routing problems, which can be related to the computational complexity of finding exact solutions.
